            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-1029] Update 3.x legacy homepage with end of life notification and pointer to HTTPComponents</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-1029</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>If you google for &amp;quot;http client&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;httpclient&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;apache http client&amp;quot; the first result is always legacy Commons-HttpClient page.  If you follow the link, there&amp;#39;s no indication whatsoever on the legacy page that its not the latest version, or that it&amp;#39;s end-of-lifed.  Unless you&amp;#39;re already aware of HttpComponents, there&amp;#39;s no obvious way to find it from the legacy page.  The only reference to HttpComponents is actually in the &amp;#39;History&amp;#39; section.  &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The source for the legacy page should be updated to indicate Commons-HttpClient is an end-of-lifed project and should provide a pointer to the new HttpComponents page in a more prominent location.</description>
